We rescue robots.

Adagy Robotics is a 24/7 remote intervention service for your robots. When your robot fails, it can call out to Adagy over our API. Our trained operators will take over and drive your robot back to a stable state, and then resume autonomous operation.

Meet the Adagy team

We love robots, and we want to see them everywhere. We started Adagy because we understand that reliability is critical to the success of the industry.

Ros Shinkle

Co-Founder and CEO

Former Staff Robotics Engineer at Boston Dynamics. Ros engineered the algorithms to make Boston Dynamics' Spot inspect factory lines with its arm.

Kathleen Brandes

Co-Founder and CTO

Former Senior Machine Learning Engineer at Tesla. Kathleen engineered the algorithms for lane changes for Tesla Autopilot, which drives >1,000,000 miles a day.

Frequently Asked Questions

How does an Adagy rescue work?

When a robot fails, it makes a request to Adagy via our API. Adagy routes the distress call to a trained robot operator in our call center. The Adagy operator analyzes the failure, takes control of the robot, and remotely drives the robot back to a stable state.

Will using Adagy complicate my customers' IT requirements?

We are pursuing SOC2 compliance today. And we'll guarantee a 1 day turnaround time for IT audits by new customers.

Will I know when Adagy takes control of the robot in my facility?

Adagy operators notify the site owner when they've taken control. Adagy operators also prepare failure summaries after the fact.
